=Edward Hetzel Schafer (1913-1991)=
===Keywords===
[[杜綰]]
==Publications==
===Monographs===
* The Empire of Min. Tokyo: Rutland, 1954
* Yu Wan's Stone Catalogue of Cloudy Forest: A Commentary and Synopsis. Berkeley: University of California, 1961
* The Golden Peaches of Samarkand: A Study of T'ang Exotics. Berkeley: University of California Press, 1963, 1985
* The Vermilion Bird: T'ang Images of the South. Berkeley: University of California Press, 1967
* Shore of Pearls. Berkeley: University of California Press, 1970
* The Divine Woman: Dragon Ladies and Rain Maidens in T'ang Literature. Berkeley: University of California Press, 1973
* Pacing the Void: T'ang Approaches to the Stars. Berkeley: University of California Press, 1977
* Mirages on the Sea of Time: Poetry of Ts'ao T'ang. Berkeley: University of California Press, 1985
===Articles===
* A Trip to the Moon. JAOS 96.1 (1976): 27-37
* The Cranes of Mao shan. In Tantric and Taoist Studies. Bruxelles, 1983
